  "event_preview": "Suzuka International Racing Course is a 5.807 km (3.609 mi) figure-eight road course in Suzuka, Mie Prefecture — one of the most demanding layouts in Japanese motorsport, with the famous Spoon Curve, 130R and the Degner esses. Rounds 4 and 5 of the 2026 Super Formula Championship take place on 23–24 May at Suzuka, which returns to the calendar after the season opened at Motegi while the usual Suzuka slot was displaced by the rescheduled Formula 1 Japanese Grand Prix.\n\nEach race runs over 50 laps (290.4 km) with a mandatory pit window opening on lap 11. Qualifying uses the series' three-stage knockout format (Q1 / Q2), with championship bonus points for the top three qualifiers. The all-time qualifying lap record at Suzuka belongs to Tomoki Nojiri (1:35.672, 2023); the race lap record is 1:36.757 (Tomoki Nojiri, 2023).",
